increments was used to identify 2-h periods in the 8 h before calving with 82.8\% sensitivity and 80.4\% specificity. Changes in behavior and machine-learning alerts indicate that commercially marketed behavioral monitors may have calving prediction potential. [ABSTRACT FROM AUTHOR]},
